text: In the cooked-dish section of a supermarket, side dishes are sold. You can buy them, bring them home, and eat a meal without cooking. Common side dishes are fried foods (such as croquettes), yakitori (grilled chicken), nimono (boiled dishes), and salads. Supermarkets sell common side dishes that families often make at home and hard-to-prepare side dishes that are not easily made at home.
